ctive</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    GUM<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-GUM\"> </a></td><td>ChewingGum</td><td>A sweetened and flavored insoluble plastic material of various shapes which when chewed, releases a drug substance into the oral cavity.</td><td>14496</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    PAD<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-PAD\"> </a></td><td>Pad</td><td/><td>14497</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      MEDPAD<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-MEDPAD\"> </a></td><td>Medicated Pad</td><td/><td>14498</td><td>active</td><td/><td>PAD</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    PATCH<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-PATCH\"> </a></td><td>Patch</td><td>A drug delivery system that contains an adhesived backing and that permits its ingredients to diffuse from some portion of it (e.g., the backing itself, a reservoir, the adhesive, or some other component) into the body from the external site where it is applied.</td><td>14499</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      TPATCH<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-TPATCH\"> </a></td><td>Transdermal Patch</td><td/><td>14500</td><td>active</td><td/><td>PATCH</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        TPATH16<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-TPATH16\"> </a></td><td>16 Hour Transdermal Patch</td><td/><td>14501</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TPATCH</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        TPATH24<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-TPATH24\"> </a></td><td>24 Hour Transdermal Patch</td><td/><td>14502</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TPATCH</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        TPATH2WK<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-TPATH2WK\"> </a></td><td>Biweekly Transdermal Patch</td><td/><td>14505</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TPATCH</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        TPATH72<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-TPATH72\"> </a></td><td>72 Hour Transdermal Patch</td><td/><td>14503</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TPATCH</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        TPATHWK<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-TPATHWK\"> </a></td><td>Weekly Transdermal Patch</td><td/><td>14504</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TPATCH</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    PELLET<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-PELLET\"> </a></td><td>Pellet</td><td>A small sterile solid mass consisting of a highly purified drug (with or without excipients) made by the formation of granules, or by compression and molding.</td><td>14533</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    PILL<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-PILL\"> </a></td><td>Pill</td><td>A small, round solid dosage form containing a medicinal agent intended for oral administration.</td><td>14506</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      CAP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-CAP\"> </a></td><td>Capsule</td><td>A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container or \"shell\" made from a suitable form of gelatin.</td><td>14507</td><td>active</td><td/><td>PILL</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        ORCAP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ORCAP\"> </a></td><td>Oral Capsule</td><td/><td>14508</td><td>active</td><td/><td>CAP</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          ENTCAP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ENTCAP\"> </a></td><td>Enteric Coated Capsule</td><td/><td>14509</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORCAP</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            ERENTCAP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERENTCAP\"> </a></td><td>Extended Release Enteric Coated Capsule</td><td/><td>14510</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ENTCAP, ERCAP</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          ERCAP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERCAP\"> </a></td><td>Extended Release Capsule</td><td>A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container made from a suitable form of gelatin, and which releases a drug (or drugs) in such a manner to allow a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug (or drugs) presented as a conventional dosage form.</td><td>14511</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORCAP</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            ERCAP12<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERCAP12\"> </a></td><td>12 Hour Extended Release Capsule</td><td/><td>14513</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ERCAP</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            ERCAP24<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERCAP24\"> </a></td><td>24 Hour Extended Release Capsule</td><td/><td>14514</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ERCAP</td></tr><tr style=\"background-color: #ffeeee\"><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            ERECCAP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERECCAP\"> </a></td><td>Extended Release Enteric Coated Capsule</td><td>*Rationale:* Duplicate of code ERENTCAP. Use code ERENTCAP instead.</td><td>14512</td><td>retired</td><td/><td>ERCAP</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            <a href=\"#v3-orderableDrugForm-ERENTCAP\">ERENTCAP</a></td><td>Extended Release Enteric Coated Capsule</td><td colspan=\"5\"/></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      TAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-TAB\"> </a></td><td>Tablet</td><td>A solid dosage form containing medicinal substances with or without suitable diluents.</td><td>14515</td><td>active</td><td/><td>PILL</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        ORTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ORTAB\"> </a></td><td>Oral Tablet</td><td/><td>14516</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          BUCTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-BUCTAB\"> </a></td><td>Buccal Tablet</td><td/><td>14518</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            SRBUCTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-SRBUCTAB\"> </a></td><td>Sustained Release Buccal Tablet</td><td/><td>14519</td><td>active</td><td/><td>BUCTAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          CAPLET<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-CAPLET\"> </a></td><td>Caplet</td><td/><td>14517</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          CHEWTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-CHEWTAB\"> </a></td><td>Chewable Tablet</td><td>A solid dosage form containing medicinal substances with or without suitable diluents that is intended to be chewed, producing a pleasant tasting residue in the oral cavity that is easily swallowed and does not leave a bitter or unpleasant after-taste.</td><td>14520</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          CPTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-CPTAB\"> </a></td><td>Coated Particles Tablet</td><td/><td>14521</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          DISINTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-DISINTAB\"> </a></td><td>Disintegrating Tablet</td><td>A solid dosage form containing medicinal substances which disintegrates rapidly, usually within a matter of seconds, when placed upon the tongue.</td><td>14523</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          DRTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-DRTAB\"> </a></td><td>Delayed Release Tablet</td><td/><td>14522</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          ECTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ECTAB\"> </a></td><td>Enteric Coated Tablet</td><td/><td>14524</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            ERECTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERECTAB\"> </a></td><td>Extended Release Enteric Coated Tablet</td><td/><td>14525</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ECTAB, ERTAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          ERTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERTAB\"> </a></td><td>Extended Release Tablet</td><td>A solid dosage form containing a drug which allows at least a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug presented in conventional dosage form.</td><td>14526</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            ERTAB12<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERTAB12\"> </a></td><td>12 Hour Extended Release Tablet</td><td/><td>14528</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ERTAB</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            ERTAB24<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ERTAB24\"> </a></td><td>24 Hour Extended Release Tablet</td><td/><td>14527</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ERTAB</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">            <a href=\"#v3-orderableDrugForm-ERECTAB\">ERECTAB</a></td><td>Extended Release Enteric Coated Tablet</td><td colspan=\"5\"/></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          ORTROCHE<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-ORTROCHE\"> </a></td><td>Lozenge/Oral Troche</td><td>A solid preparation containing one or more medicaments, usually in a flavored, sweetened base which is intended to dissolve or disintegrate slowly in the mouth.</td><td>14530</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">          SLTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-SLTAB\"> </a></td><td>Sublingual Tablet</td><td/><td>14531</td><td>active</td><td/><td>ORTAB</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        VAGTAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-VAGTAB\"> </a></td><td>Vaginal Tablet</td><td/><td>14532</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TAB</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    POWD<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-POWD\"> </a></td><td>Powder</td><td>An intimate mixture of dry, finely divided drugs and/or chemicals that may be intended for internal or external use.</td><td>14534</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      TOPPWD<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-TOPPWD\"> </a></td><td>Topical Powder</td><td/><td>14535</td><td>active</td><td/><td>POWD</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        RECPWD<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-RECPWD\"> </a></td><td>Rectal Powder</td><td/><td>14536</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TOPPWD</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">        VAGPWD<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-VAGPWD\"> </a></td><td>Vaginal Powder</td><td/><td>14537</td><td>active</td><td/><td>TOPPWD</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    SUPP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-SUPP\"> </a></td><td>Suppository</td><td>A solid body of various weights and shapes, adapted for introduction into the rectal, vaginal, or urethral orifice of the human body; they usually melt, soften, or dissolve at body temperature.</td><td>14538</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      RECSUPP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-RECSUPP\"> </a></td><td>Rectal Suppository</td><td/><td>14539</td><td>active</td><td/><td>SUPP</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      URETHSUPP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-URETHSUPP\"> </a></td><td>Urethral suppository</td><td/><td>14541</td><td>active</td><td/><td>SUPP</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      VAGSUPP<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-VAGSUPP\"> </a></td><td>Vaginal Suppository</td><td/><td>14540</td><td>active</td><td/><td>SUPP</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    SWAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-SWAB\"> </a></td><td>Swab</td><td>A wad of absorbent material usually wound around one end of a small stick and used for applying medication or for removing material from an area.</td><td>14542</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      MEDSWAB<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-MEDSWAB\"> </a></td><td>Medicated swab</td><td/><td>14543</td><td>active</td><td/><td>SWAB</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    WAFER<a name=\"v3-orderableDrugForm-WAFER\"> </a></td><td>Wafer</td><td>A thin slice of material containing a medicinal agent.</td><td>14544</td><td>active</td><td/><td>_SolidDrugForm</td></tr></table></div>"
  ] ;
